 || (Ngwar Bo Mee)Client Visit: Looking for a Director of Project Management who is quite entrepreneurial, adaptable, accountable and driven, and is keen to grow tremendously with soon to be full fledged start-up firm

- late twenties to mid thirties candidates (28 - 35) who are in Project Management Supervisor level/ middle management level, not in senior management and can set-up entire project management department hiring
- Quantity Surveyor/Purchasing and Site Supervisors and Engineers
- do Master Schedule 
-  Liaise with all vendors and Subcontractors, Site engineers and site supervisors
-  Control Budget and Schedule
- Purchase all materials 
- Create costing based on construction documents 
and has Knowledge of Auto-cad, Microsoft Projects (Or similar Project Management Software).

Expat who lives in the country 2-3 yrs is fine. If local, then great.

Salary:3-3.5 K + Bonus + Departmental Profit Sharing.

Salary can be doubled within a year if the department performs well. Can receive 8 - 10 K a month in 2-3 yrs time.

 || (May Phoo Kywe)Client Visit: 30.3.2016

KTZ is founded by U Kyaw Thein Zan (MD) and U Than Ag (GM) in 1994. Very local and traditional company but planning to step into international standard. 

Businesses are
- Pharmaceutical (300+ SKUs)
- Electronics 
- Implants

Pharmaceutical companies in Myanmar are very reliable on CRM. They want to change it because the process is like one client will be owned by one staff - if someone leaves the business is done. 

Government is encouraging them to set up a factory (will be soon)

450 Manpower (to be 500 next year)

Marketing team - 9 teams (20+ personnels in each team)
- Nationwide (14 cities across the countries)
- Ygn, Mdy, NPT, MGW, Monywa, MKN, TGI, LSH, Myeik, Dawei... (10 - 20 staffs in each city)

Competitor - AA Medical, DKSH, Mega

*They are looking for a marketing manager who can take care of the nationwide marketing teams.
- The role is to replace a German Marketing Manager (who stays with the group for only 3 months and left because of the culture clash.
- Can review weekly and monthly KPIs
- Can set up Marketing Plan
- Report to GM and MD
- work together with Business Opertions Manager and Product Manager
- Must have pharma knowledge
- Prefer expats (Indian or Philipino)
- Salary increment every 6 months.
- Commission Quarterly

Date added: 2015-07-23 || Action: Client Visit || Wants a BDManager 
Preferably, local/ repat single female in her twenties/ thirties who is verbal, proactive, communicative, result oriented, self driven
Reporting to Ken, Kwong and commercial manager (possibly)
Need urgent

Budget : 1- 4 K based on experience
Minimum 2-3 years of experience in BD - Oil & Gas/ Construction/ Telecommunication

Date added: 2015-07-20 || Action: Appointment || Met a few times at the British Chamber, had lots of lunches and so forth now and hopefully he will get us on as a client! Nice guy, a party guy I think who is very busy and always running around. Likes people to be professional but also play hard and work hard. 
Date added: 2015-07-20 || Action: Client Visit || Met again with Kwong - looks like we will get signed terms tomorrow morning which is great. notes below on the BD manager job that we will start with - salary is low but said we can do future larger ones if we do this well:

young dynamic, getting convos with bigger companies, not 20 years exp. 

can react to different demands and situations, cash be flexible adaptable and good initiative 

more communicative, outgoing, assertive, and talkative. pro-active.  need to be active in discussions, good follow up, able to look at the small picture and big picture, mainly the small picture like operational issues. good grasp of the business. not a 9-5 job. 

looking to develop independent projects, tender projects, could be many things, currently 3 large tender projects, not just acquiring business but also closing the business. 

salary: 1-4K, cant go over 4K - benefits can be negotiated. possible housing but depends on the situation. 

areas for progression: depends on performance, only two ken and kwong or possibly the commercial manager: she is is a good local. 

2-3 years of experience minimum, open to diffifernt industries, telecoms etc. ideally a female - needs to keep it very professional and last time they had someone doing sleazy meetings. really good follow up skills.

asap. 

currently team is two assistant managers and need either one more or manager. 

must be convincing, must be able to tell a story, have to be persuasive. 

female ams who is systematic - 

20% travelling - no family ideally.

Date added: 2015-07-23 || Action: Email || 23rd July 2015 - I contacted Ben to see if they wanted us to open up the search for the local lawyer again as they had to previously put it on hold because they were waiting for payments from clients. This is what he said:

"Yes, our clients were very slow on that particular occasion but they came through with payment in the end, so accounts are looking much healthier.  Actually we are in the process of pitching for some new work and if we get it, its likely that hiring a new Myanmar lawyer will become a priority.

Perhaps I can get in touch with you after our recent pitches have been made - I don't want to waste your time in the interim."

 || (Ngwar Bo Mee)Client Visit: Mitsubishi

Met Thiri on 6/5/2016.
Only one HR on the ground - herself. Her director directly recruited her. Will share Aquila profile and terms to her boss.

Staff must be willing to go beyond his JD due to company culture. No director role in the company, only Manager  mostly internally promoted. Rank is determined with Hays Scale. Use Japanese firms and 3 local job boards  not happy with CDC  delay in response and providing candidates. HQ provides managerial candidates. 

Asked the list of clients and said its difficult for them to choose supplier without it and all suppliers provides it. Dropped Apollo name only. 
Strange system, they never sign on the term until they have interviewed candidates put forward and taken a candidate on board to examine quality. Told her we cannot accept it and we dont compromise on quality and can read testimonials from clients.

Identity (Passport, ID)
Banking (Credit cards, Debit cards or POM) and 
Telecom (Sim card).
They are here to look for market opportunities and innitial market research (not in depth). Pat comes to Yangon 4 times a year starting two years ago. There are 6,500 man power throughout the world, in which 1,000 is in Asia. A leading player in technology with a Head Office in France. 

They are looking into 3 years time for the whole office set up in Myanmar. Need someone ( a local who has very good connection with the military and ministries) on the ground after election to do IMR without any physical investment in 6 months time.

Priorities for them is to
1. Get in contact with IT recruitment company if possible.
2. Apply for Local License with the help of a local company/ foreign company who they can partner with

Date added: 2015-09-21 || Action: Client Visit || Met Telenor HR  -  Poh Poh Myint, Lei Wah Wah + 1 on 17/9/2015 at 11 a.m.

Usually promote senior level positions internally. They use other recruitment firms for mid level positions.

They use Local firms;
	CDC
	MyJobs
& International firms
	Wenham Carter (England)  got returnees from them
	 Quest ontheFRONTIER (Singapore)  got repats

Pay maximum 20% for the recruitment service charge. 
60 days payment term - not the Invoice date, the actual commencement date by the candidate.
Its been already 2 months they are doing Headcount and restructuring. Need manpower (must be local, repat even better) for
	Voice & data  already approached SAMSUNG & Technology companies
	Senior Lawyer 
	Cluster Head  can be from parallel industry in Sales & Marekting (FMCG, Pharmaceutical and so on) 5  6 years ofof experience

Avoid Headhunting from 
	Their vendors
	Competitors (Ooredoo & MPT)

PanAsia and MIC are OK to headhunt

Telenor HR team will join Top Career Myanmar Job Fair in Singapore on 19 Sep. They held job fair in Aug 2014 and also join CDC last April. So this will be the third time. But they are not very positive about this event particularly. 


Chloe offers 20% for mid level, but for senior position, will have a chat with them upon their return from Singapore Job Fair. They look interested to use our firm.

English (need a lot of improvement)

 || (Ngwar Bo Mee)Client Visit: Met with Amy on 17/6/2016.

Must find a strong candidate before mid of July as the application deadline is end of July. 

Looking for a whole new crew to participate Phandeyeer Accelerator Program (wants to see success start-up stories) with "Business in the Box" (got validation from Silicon Valley a year ago that it is quite advanced), in which she is a mentor & BoD and is a Secretary of Phandeyeer. 
She has to hand over everything to the team to start a separate company for "Business in the box" . Most of the participants who will be pitching to be selected for the program have been together working on a specific project for so long. So she is a bit worry on the new team potential collaboration in the competition. 

Accelerator is a unique opportunity for those IT professional who wants to know the whole process of taking the business from the ground to the top. All the necessary support IT gurus, industrial specialists will be given from the program including monetary - 2 million dollar from ebay co-founder for this Accelerator program - 6 months program to be seated in Phandeeyar office (mentioned on TechAsia). 200,000 USD for each selected start-up. 

Needs BD/ Product Lead - 2500 Max
Technical Lead - between 700 & 1000
Software Developer - between 200 & 400
2 Sales Executive - between 300 & 500

Will offer usual pay + dividends to the whole team at the end of the day to have ownership on the success of the product.

Andra is like second in command at Netsmart taking care of business operations in Myanmar. 


Business In the Box is Cloud, ERP & Server. Can build anything like CRM in it. Use less space and can operate with an Inverter whole day even if there is electricity break out. 

A lot of investors eyeing on this product. She doesn't want to introduce it to the market until the product has been taken off internally. 


Will help with product lead only - must optimize
- Sales
- BD
- Product Development
- Client accounts - SME

Amy & Andy will give additional support when necessary. 

Repat - prefer
Expat - cost goes up (one translator has to be matched)

 || (Ngwar Bo Mee)Outbound Call: Talked to Somphot on the phone 5/11/2015.
They really cannot bring up the budget for Deputy Chief Rep to 3500 USD Net.  So gave my apology for not being able to find the right candidate within that range as all of the potential candidates I've interviewed min salary they are currently receiving is like 3000 USD, some even 4000 USD. 
Somphot said he looks forward to working together with us in the future and he is sorry too.
contact-comment:
Date added: 2015-11-10 || Action: Outbound Call || Talked to Somphot on the phone 5/11/2015.
They really cannot bring up the budget for Deputy Chief Rep to 3500 USD Net.  So gave my apology for not being able to find the right candidate within that range as all of the potential candidates I've interviewed min salary they are currently receiving is like 3000 USD, some even 4000 USD.

Date added: 2015-09-24 || Action: Outbound Call || Talked to Somphot on Viber for 15 mins on 23/9/2015.

Very nice person to talk to. Connection wasn't good enough to hear clearly. 

Thai Life Insurance 
- got license from Myanmar Government to open the Representative Office in June 2015.
- will get offie in 2 weeks (Backer McKenzie is helping them with it
- will do both general insurance and life insurance as life insurance is not well known in Myanmar yet. 
- believe theyll perform better then the rest 14 foreign insurance firms as Myanmar has similar culture and tradition and the market is not advanced like western at all. Its in her infancy state.
- Deputy Chief Rep from Myanmar will Report to Chief Rep in Bangkok. 
- The team in Bangkok will visit Myanmar quarterly a year. Its not fixed like only they will come to Myanmar. Deputy Chief Rep will also visit Bkk for business. So it's flexible.
- No gender preference as long as they can do market research, do marketing and liaise with the stakeholders  government, financial institutions and give awareness to the general public without generating any revenue. 
- dont know when theyll open branch yet in Myanmar. 
It solely depends on Governments approval as they have announced not to give permit to any foreign firms in 2015 as theyve already given permission to do direct underwriting in Thilawa to three Japanese insurers. 
- Budget 1000  1500 USD net. Told him to leave it open for discussion based on candidates expertise and potential.

 || (Ngwar Bo Mee)Client Visit: Met Mona with Chloe on 1/10/2015 at 2 p.m at BASF office at Sedona Hotel.
Very active and speak short to the point.  Want to use Aquila to recruit mid level positions - one Senior Sales Executive/ Sales Manager for Mining and one for Agriculture.
Has used other recruitment firms in Myanmar, but not happy with the result. 
Mona will submit Aquila profile and terms to Thai Office for legal matter to do background checks. Will get back to us in 2 weeks. 

Mining 
- must be from Engineering background
- can be repat/ local (read & write Burmese and fluent English)
- report to Director in Australia
- instructions will be given by oversea offices ( especially from Hong Kong and Thailand)
- 3- 4 years of experience in Mining

Agriculture
- must have local sales experience (3-4 years) and can travel around the country
- can be repat/ local (read & write Burmese and fluent English)
- report to Director in Singapore 
- instructions will be given by oversea offices ( especially from Hong Kong and Thailand)
- flexible, outgoing and good communications

 || (Ngwar Bo Mee)Email: Easy Asset Management part of management Financial Group, founded in 2005, is the leading Bulgarian company for home credits (registered non-bank financial institution). In Bulgaria the company operates under the brand of Easy Credit. Outside Bulgaria the organization is expanding its operations and market penetration under the brand of iCredit. Easy Credit and iCredit employ more than 6900 employees and associates in 270 offices across Bulgaria, Ukraine, Romania, Poland, Czech Republic and Macedonia. 

Now we are approaching our next step of international expansion in the ASEAN region and we are exploring the opportunity to start operations in Myanmar. 


1. Has the company already received Microfinance licence in Myanmar? 
No, there are few options that we explore how to proceed

2. Will Easy Asset Management be operated in Myanmar under the brand of iCredit? So how will it be different from other microfinance firms here?

The brand will be iCredit

3. To whom will the General Manager be reporting to? 

The GM will report to the International Development Director at iCredit International/Easy Asset Management

4. Do GM and Operation Manager need to do domestic travelling and international or only based in Yangon? 

Domestic travelling will be required. The international traveling will be up to twice per year for the biannual intentional meetings (3 days/meeting)

 5. Does Office location, set up and everything have to be done by GM with the help of OM? 

Yes, plus the needed local contractors support when/where needed

6. What are the vision and long term plan for Myanmar? 

To become national represented company in the 5th year (to have offices in each large city of Myanmar)

7. How is the culture of iCredit like in ASEAN region? 

International/corporate culture with strong entrepreneurial spirit, results oriented

8. After testing the depth of the water, how quickly will you expand the team?

In the first 5 years the growth (the expansion of the branch/office network) will be slow - approximately 5 to 10 new branches/offices per year

9. How quickly do you need to fill in those positions? 

After the elections in Myanmar

10. Are there fixed budget for these two positions?

No, we will address the local standard remuneration levels
    
11. Any gender preference?

Usually it turns out that there are more male suitable candidates, however we will review male and female candidates no matter of their gender

 || (Ngwar Bo Mee)Client Visit: Will go to Naypyidaw to meet with regulator on 3rd Feb. So need in house lawyer to advise them before them and to meet with the regulators too. Took MFI license in order to operate as a foreign entity. More like a consumer finance (much like what AEON is doing); giving personal loan. Have 2 business registered - Dr.Cash and LeadGeneration (Consultancy). Don't want to use External counsel as they won't hold accountable for the possible bad outcomes later like jail term. Knows Myanmar doesn't have practise law in Online Consumer Finance, so want to make a scheme and present the regulator to make sure that their operations is within the legal frame. Dino is also involve in bringing the ideas up and will be CEO of one entity and advisor of consumer finance. Not sure their model - scheme - used in 4 Billion Lending Club (USA) would work in Myanmar. Indonesia, Thailand use it. 

For operations, want someone with call centre experience.

 || (Chloe Williamson)Client Visit: Met with Dave and Andy at the Kandawgyi palace hotel. Really nice guys, straight to the point and no BS. 

New role and info about the company:
Tin and tungsten industry, it comes out of the ground and then concentrated through their plant, normally about 65% metal content. They have a plant in Dawei to split the tin from the tungsten, currently there are 2 areas in myanmar for this work, one in dawei and one in mochie (kachin?). Theya re then exporting the materials. Over the last 9 months commodity prices have dropped drastically everywhere in the world and so they are looking to re-direct their business model. Currently the factory/plant is massively under capacity. All mining companies in myanmar are taxed at source. Everyone is currently stock-piling, especially the government in myanmar. Their first option for the new business direction is to do JV's with other mining companies. Andy is a process engineer, but if they bring in their technology from overseas they could do all of the processing here, average currently is 50% in myanmar and the rest gets thrown away and left to scavengers. In the UK the minimum normally kept is 90%. Will be becoming more asset based as they structure. 12-15 people already in the office, only western company in myanmar to try and work in this area (mining). The ministry is complicated, MEZ is most relevant, each ME has its own MD and they report back to the ministery. DG of the ministry looks after all of 6 which is the most relevant to mining. They already have contacts on a technical level but not at policitical level - could be really useful. Bodwin company info-, started in 1910, largest lead production company  worldwide, nickel project very famous, all 3 big ones went to the first myanmar holdings company - all generals and other military. 
deal opportunity for them is endless, ideas for expansion totally open. Another business direction for them is the analytical services side of the business - ready to launch this in myanmar, this is the lab that they can say what the metal content is in the rock, only labs currently doing this now are givernment owned and take too long and are not accurate. SGS: MNC laboratory but doing no analysis here, they only do the preparation and then they send it off. 
30 million tonnes out of dawei pre WW2 - now only 1.5 million. 
Bodwin - used to have 6 loco-motives and stopped in 1880, put a 10 tonne truck on the rails instead, changed the transmission and still like this today (!!!) - so much opportunity in myanmar for this type of work. current office is in east dagon, will need to move this. Trading business being run through Thurag UST, U soe Paing which is the company that they are currently buying. 



Looking for:
Government relations, myanmar business knowledge, andy will be moving here full time so its going to be working with him closely, must have 100% perfect english, knowledge of mining is a plus, good attitude, entrepreneurship, critical thinking, purely deal making, someone that wants to build something, very entrepreneurial, 5 year gig minimum, no benefit package, just straight forward base. travelling domestically only. must be a self starter, 

Ideas
Aung khine
shine
nyantha maw lin
moe thauk

Date added: 2015-12-15 || Action: Client Visit || Going over messages back and forth for a month and finally met him at British Chamber Network Event on 14/12/2015. Looks very knowledgable and has lots of powerful connections ...

Office in Novotel (4th Floor)

Developer (built Rosehill)
FMCG  family owned (Aung sth ... I can't recall the name)  been in the market for over 30 years 
2 cement plants  Taunggyi and Mandalay/ Yangon (not sure) (worked with KBZ group)
Director for IKBZ (needs a MD)
Need local, preferably repats
	1 CEO and CFO for Rosehill 
	1 CFO for FMCG and construction

Keeps comparing culture difference between Lafarge and local business 

Said he has sent his staff from local management under Lafarge, but didnt last even 2 months. Said he needs skilled management staff to bring changes in the company, but still insists keeping the traditional way. 
Doesnt want huge pay gap between new comer, CFO and current staff as he thinks it will destroy their mentality those who stick with them for over 2 decades .. Compares 1000 and 5000 USD because salary confidentiality is problematic in Myanmar. If he were to fire those who share salary info, said there wont be anyone left working for him. 

But for Rosehill (1 CEO and 1 CFO), he doesnt care about the salary gap as its newly built.

 || (Ngwar Bo Mee)Client Visit: Met Kaung Naing Soe at their office in 9 Miles with Jolyn and May Phoo. Has been working for MK distribution over 13 years now. Joined as a marketing executive and promoted to DMD and given shares. Super positive about company's growth, said it's 30 - 60% every year. This year 60%  growth and more added portfolio - Lubricant (Castrol - UK) nationwide and Telenor (sim card + top up card) in Yangon region. Produce MAMA in Yangon, has factory in Mandalay ..... 500 staff at factory. 450 Distribution staff ... 300 loyal staff (8 years in MK distribution). Export their products to Bangladesh, Singapore, Middle East and Malaysia through wholesaler. Planning to get listed on Thailand and Yangon Stock Exchange as they've got reputation in Thai. MK founded in 1990, MK distribution founded in 2004 and distributed their own products (Ayawaddy)... started diverse business model in 2012  and started distributing others' products...idea came from MK 2nd generation .. sons. Has 48 subsidiaries.... Local centric. Not much staff turn-over rate as they practice decentralization system and build a sense of belonging and team. Need search help in expanding new business - Lubricant Castrol (will coordinate with Bosch probably .... smiling while saying that)
Need one person for each position (Myanmar - local only)
Marketing Manager
Sales Manager
Technical Manager (Engineering Background)

Now MK whole group is connected together. HR handles all the recruitment matters - in house and use local recruitment firms - work.com, myjobs.com. Senior positions are no necessary to fill up, no one leaves.

 || (Ngwar Bo Mee)Client Visit: Met him at Rose Hill office in Novotel with May Phoo.
Appointment was to meet with Ko Min Thant, but he has got an urgent meeting and couldn't join.
Traditional and humble. AMT was founded 40 years in Myanmar, but founded as an official group in 2005.
Decision making power is centralized by the MD and ever changing. So wants those 4 persons - 2 CEOs and 2 CFOs who can bring changes to the orgazination (family centric), can discuss & argue with MD- U Hla Myo, AMT Group.

HQ for AMT is in Mandalay, very conservative place. Off days only on Sabbath day (not Sat & Sundays) due to the culture out there. In Yangon, half day on Sat. Still setting IT, so very bad email address and no websites right now.

AMT Global listed somewhere
AMT Group listed in YSX.

Different business under ATM group

- Aung Myin Thu (Construction & Real Estate Development Co., Ltd)
- Auspicious Millennium Trading Group Co.,Ldd (Palm Oil - AMT is one of the five accredited Palm Oil Importers throughout Myanmar)
- Royal Oil Group Co., Ltd (Palm Oil-Importer)
- CommonWealth Industry Company Limited
- CommonWealth Rice & Padding Co., Ltd (Exporter) - Ko Hla Myo is one of the founders and shareholders of MAPCO)
- Aye Chan MG Transit (Bus, including highway from Mandalay to Bagan, Inle, Nyaung Oo, Nay Pyi Daw)

Has two separate business one family owned AMT group and Rose Hill Group, one of the four BODs and shareholders.  

AMT Group (not a holding yet) - Chairman: U Saw Nyein, focus on buying properties across Myanmar
MD - U Hla Myo, diversifying business and making new investments
Director - Ko Min Thant, running the business and working hand in hand with KBZ for cement projects (Sin Minn & KBZ Cement, and JV with Larfarge Holcim) and Insurance (IKBZ) and meet with foreign investors

Rose Hill Holding, a luxury property management and developer (1 square feet 300 USD) - apply tenders for developing Real Estate, doing JVs and working  as BODs with foreign investor, is owned by 4 local business leaders - U Zaw Zaw from Max, U Sai from Loi Hein, U Zaw Win Shein from Ayeyarhintha and U Hla Myo from AMT group. 

1 CEO and 1 CFO for Rose Hill Holding - Rose Hill Residence is built in JV with Soilbuild - 60% Soilbuild and 40% Rose Hill holding (owns the land). Management support comes from Singapore office. Spent 1 million USD in marketing, which wasn't effective at all due to lack of local content and knowledge. 

Undergoing one JV with a Japan company on a project (can't disclose the name yet)

Mingalar Zay Thit is built in corporation with YCDC, steel structure.

Organization Structure

Chairman
MD
D
GM
DGM/AGM
Managers for each unit
Executives and assistants
Has over 300 office staffs right now, not including hard labor for planting Rubber, Eucalyptus trees and Teak.

contact-comment:
Date added: 2016-09-22 || Action: Outbound Call || Positive feedback from Vivek on his Skype interview with Rupesh. Next steps will include interview with the CEO and Chairman, including a face to face interview in Myanmar.
Date added: 2016-09-16 || Action: Outbound Call || Called Vivek to get an update on Meliisa Lascano and the L&D profiles. He is ill and at home with a high fever and has requested to call back on Monday.
Date added: 2016-09-15 || Action: Outbound Call || Called Vivek to get an update on Melissa Lascano, the 2 L&D profiles and Su Myat but no answer.
Date added: 2016-09-12 || Action: Outbound Call || Called Vivek to get an update on Melissa's Skype chat with Vivian. He hasn't heard anything yet as he has been travelling. Also, told him about Yee Mon Kyaw's profile that will be sent to him for the L&D role.
Date added: 2016-09-11 || Action: Inbound Call || Called re Victor. Victor is not going forward for the role anymore.
IBTC is not considering the other 3 candidates: Karen, Steve and Snow. Karen and Steve are more on Channel Marketing. Snow is a generalist. They are looking for someone who is a specialist.

Date added: 2016-09-07 || Action: Client Visit || Accompanied Nat to meet with Vivek on 25 Aug to propose the RPO solution. Vivek needs to discuss it with the senior management at TPG and will get back
Date added: 2016-06-08 || Action: Client Visit || Nice guy - quite punchy and obviously very senior in TPG. Looking atter supply chain and procurement function for investments globally. 

Head of SC for IBTC now is Aung Kyaw Moe (procurement and logistics together), new hire of a lady called Nandar (head of procurement) who reports to AKM. She is in her 30's, young and excited, very talented but over her head, most of her direct reports are more traditional and focused on delivery and chasing vendors. They have launched an E-vendor project which is the firts of its kind in Myanmar, its allining new vendors and monitoring existing vendors. The new role is focusing on the economics, so identifying new vendors, managing productivity and analyzing all existing vendors for the business - pricing and valuing analysis. 

It needs to be someone who can help nanadar train and develp her team, ideally from an MNC environment, procurement background. English most important, idelaly repat could be expat. Global skills set and needs to be able to handle all international suppliers, as well as the few in Myanmar (EG Broken rice which is a major feed stock). 

This needs ot be a hire that does not push nandar out of a job, they dont want to slit the team at this stage and currently its already split by category - eg bottles, lables, caps. nandar has 13 years of expeirnece in total. target Unilever, P&G, Coke, Nesle etc. Need CV's by next Thursday. 

This person would get the international training as they would be invited to the chief procurement summit for TPG in Shanghai each year also. 
Date added: 2016-06-02 || Action: Client Visit || Went to see Vivek again yesterday, went over all of the roles so far, corp Secretary very urgent, as is legal and branding and trade, rose could place but need ot get her in to interview one last time. a little annoyed with aye aye mon of course, will also put forward a proposal to train the current HRBP as well as doing 5-6 people in the HR team. 
Date added: 2016-03-18 || Action: Client Visit || Many meetings with Vivek and Vivian to negotiate terms and discuss TPG takeover at IBTC. 

Chloes client - all contact with IBTC must go directly through Chloe as they prefer one contact only. 
Date added: 2016-02-08 || Action: Client Visit || See scanned client meeting note

The company wants to hire who is able to handle start-ups and entrepreneurial professional. And people who is ready to move a step higher (senior level).

Company size in Myanmar is 30 (Expats - 8)

The vacancies at the moment are Sales Director (They have very high expectation for this position), Sales Capability Manager(who can do training - Must be a Burmese speaker with good English), Marketing Director (Expert in FMCG industry and entrepreneurial) and HR Director (Will be trained in SG every six months).

The good facts to work in Friesland are
- Opportunities to move in the group (Overseas)
- Family culture
- No big layer
- Meeting every month
- Dinner every quarter
- Employee gathering trip every year (Beach)
- Good retention (senior)

Currently, they have already talked with My Jobs (Francis) for executive search.

Prefer headhunt from:
1. Carlsberg (Same distribution style)
2. Heineken
3. Nestle (He wants HR from Nestle - Sandar Aung)
4. Unileiver
5. DKSH (to be careful when do headhunting - DKSH is their distributor)

Salary range is open.
Date added: 2016-01-21 || Action: Client Visit || Friesland Campina = merger bet Friesland Foods and Campina (2 Dutch Companies) in 2009.

In Myanmar, internal candidates struggle with security, education and infrastructure.

The company is looking for individuals(expats) who like to move and become pioneers in the country; like to
move to senior level.

They have 30 employees in Myanmar including 8 expats and 1 repat (Head of Sales)

They are looking for Sales Director, Sales Capability Manager(can do sales training), Marketing Director and HR Director(travel to Singapore every 6 months.

benefits: opportunities for regional promotion

culture: free to move around
meeting every month
dinner every quarter
employers/family gathering every year

retention rate: senior - no problem
engineers/field workers(sales and the like) - frequent (coz of the high expectations)
DSM- aim = 80 % field, 20% desk (with quality output)

Now using My jobs(Francis) for their senior positions

Careful headhunting from DKSH as they are their distributor.

*Very interested working with Aquila
**Ready to sign the terms

Each department carries its own recruitment if they need help, they reach out to HR. Senior position is directly recruited by the CEO, U Thadoe. Date added: 2016-03-22 || Action: Client Visit || Met with Khin Htike Htay, Feel Group on 18/3/2015. 

Has 2000 employees

Family type culture, trained people from delta region. However, as the business grows, they have to change it.
Want 1  2 expat f& b chain consultants to set up and upgrade system (IT) and process
	Bring new IT system and replace the manpower
	Train employee

Opened the first restaurant, Dream in 1992 and became a hit. One of the shareholder, actually, landlord became greedy so shut that business down with the agreement none of them will use Dream brand. 
Started a Burger restaurant with other shareholders  
	25% to .. (I forgot who)
	25% to landlord
	50% to U Soe Nyi Nyi (feel group founder). Other shareholders got greedy and took over operation so they left it. Was a huge success under U Soe Nyi Nyis management, once he left business, it collapsed. 


Started Feel with a focus on Burmese food + Chinese cuisine. None of the stakeholders supported their idea. However, they have survived and thrived. 
Have Feel Restaurants  in Pyin Oo Lwin, Yangon, Malawmine, Mektila and Nay Pyi Daw. Has buffet and beverage restaurant, Doreen in Wadanlan too. 

Two Franchise from abroad
	Mix Restaurant and Bar from Thai
	Miami Gray (maybe wrong spelling) from US
	Has training school, Bake with feel from Malaysia (for their employees and wannabe professionals)
	Sell
- Jura, Swiss made coffee machine
- Pregel, Italian Ice-cream shops (sell ice cream and suppy it to different   restaurants/shops too)

Has 1 central kitchen for feel Myanmar. Will open 1 more. 
Will set up two factories 

	canned food for f&b professions
	Purified Drinking Water with own brand name
	Cold storage (for cost saving). 

Khin Htike Htay, her twin sister and brother separately take care of different restaurants and business. 
Khin Htike Htay is in charge of Franchise business; Mix, Taste 1 & 2, chain in Nay Pyi Daw and Meikhtila.

Has only 18 staff. 10 in Factory and Technical Support Side and 8 in Office. Factory manager (short term) is from Thai. GM is in charge of Sika Myanmar. Chief Accountant is second in charge (hired recently and send oversea business trips to meet with HQ). 
Send oversea internal trainings, mainly to Vietnam and Thailand. If its for concrete, they send the candidate to Swiss. 

-Need one Target Market Manager
Salary is open. The last local candidate received 15 Lakh Gross (Company pays for Social Security and Income Tax). Sent 1 month Training to Vietnam and upon return to Myanmar, he left the firm as concrete is not his specialty. 

Has a senior local person. He was quite good and interested in Admin. Worked for them for 1 year and he left when they transferred him to Factory due to stress.  

Probation period is 3 months. Doesnt usually offer proposed amount. Give it after probation period based on the performance. 

GM decides salary; he submits it to Thai & Vietnam office and HQ in Swiss. So it takes sometime. 

Had bad experience with agencies in Myanmar and he prefers to do in house. But Yupa will pass on information about us and send JD for Target Market Manager.

 || (May Phoo Kywe)Client Visit: 30.3.2016 

KTZ is founded by U Kyaw Thein Zan (MD) and U Than Ag (GM) in 1994. Very local and traditional company but planning to step into international standard. 

Businesses are 
- Pharmaceutical (300+ SKUs) 
- Electronics 
- Implants 

Pharmaceutical companies in Myanmar are very reliable on CRM. They want to change it because the process is like one client will be owned by one staff - if someone leaves the business is done. 

Government is encouraging them to set up a factory (will be soon) 

450 Manpower (to be 500 next year) 

Marketing team - 9 teams (20+ personnels in each team) 
- Nationwide (14 cities across the countries) 
- Ygn, Mdy, NPT, MGW, Monywa, MKN, TGI, LSH, Myeik, Dawei... (10 - 20 staffs in each city) 

Competitor - AA Medical, DKSH, Mega 

*They are looking for a marketing manager who can take care of the nationwide marketing teams. 
- The role is to replace a German Marketing Manager (who stays with the group for only 3 months and left because of the culture clash. 
- Can review weekly and monthly KPIs 
- Can set up Marketing Plan 
- Report to GM and MD 
- work together with Business Opertions Manager and Product Manager 
- Must have pharma knowledge 
- Prefer expats (Indian or Philipino) 
- Salary increment every 6 months. 
- Commission Quarterly 

For recruitment - they are using job boards - My Jobs and Work

Date added: 2016-03-30 || Action: Client Visit || 19 Marketing Group  each group has 20 marketer including executives, supervisor and manager. Does Biannual and Annual Reports. Submit those reports to GM, HRM and MD. 

Needs one Nationwide Marketing Manager for Pharmaceutical Products  300 kinds (Title flexible) to overview and review weekly and monthly reports and make sure they are on the right track, targets and plans made one year before.
Prefers expat  European who is sharp, experienced and can adapt local culture, and has Pharmaceutical education background with 10 yrs of experience. There are between 30 & 50 staffs in K.T.Z who are doing marketing so he must be able to positively influence them. 8 yrs in FMCG and 5 yrs in Pharma is fine too. 
Must have basic knowledge in pharmacy. 

Competitors are AA, Mega and DKSH, not necessarily Rosche as they do manufacturing and marketing, distribution for themselves.  K.T.Z doesnt have factory yet, gov is enforcing though. Not sure if theyll go into that as they are not total out of touch with that one. So focus in on Marketing and Distribution (some suppliers do JV marketing and but most of them delegate the whole Mkt to them).

Has marketing personal on the ground in 14 Townships excluding Yangon. Has more or less 450 nationwide. 


Has 3 separate businesses
	Pharmaceutical  300 products
	Implant  1000 products
	Electrical

Current BD M is involved in all 3 separate businesses. Nationwide Marketing Manager will closely work with BDM & Product Manager.


Salary range: 2500  4000 USD Net + Incentives (based on subordinates performance)

HRM directly hired a German for this role with an offer for 4500 USD Net + Transportation charges. He left in 3-months as he cannot adapt the working culture  slow and relationship-based. HR M doesnt want it to happen again.
For entry-level recruitments, they use jobboards  My Jobs, work.com.

Have 3 expats, not senior roles  from Srilanka. Most of the staff is Local and Repat. Said there is a huge pool of candidate from India and Philippines within pharma industry. 

Will explain our service to MD, currently on a trip to Italy and will be back on 1 April.

 || (Ngwar Bo Mee)Client Visit: TA Resources Myanmar

Met with Ng Cheong Yew (been with the company 2 years, been in Myanmar for 4 years) on 25/5/2016.

The whole company  130 staff (Lubricants, Air Craft Lubricants and Continental - Tyre). Need one National Sales Manager (do branding too) for Continental  Tyre. Budget maximum 15 Lakh. Cannot go over that as the market is not that big and is not a GM role. Has 8 staff in Tyre business, including a very good Marketing manager. Ng Cheong Yew is leading all the business. No gender preference (seems like he prefers female due to detail-oriented sense). 
-	minimum 2 years experience
-	local (not repat as repat doesnt understand local market)
will provide a car. After 5 years of service with the company, candidate can take it home when a candidate leaves. 

Using one local search firm (charged only 2 months salary) but not satisfied with the quality of service. Have used CDC and e-search too. 

Seems like Ng Cheong Yew is open to new opportunities the way he talks. 

Recommended him to use local recruitment firms for this National sales manager role to have a wider pool of selection and also due to the limited budget they have for the role right now.

 || (Ngwar Bo Mee)Email: DO NOT APPROACH LIST and 2 BDM Role

Hi Bo Mee,
 
We had a discussion with the hiring manager and would like to provide you with some updates on the requirements of the BDM role so that you can refine your search.
 
We now have 2 openings for the BDM, one more senior and another one more junior. These 2 positions will report directly to the Key Account Director and Sales Office Manager who will be an expat in Myanmar.
 
For the senior, we need someone who is relatively senior with the right personality to be trained up to manage the Myanmar business in 2 - 3 years time. This person should have the potential to grow within Tetra Pak. The ideal experience will be around 5 - 10 years (preferred but we are open to explore more senior candidates too). As for the industry background, we would prefer someone from FMCG (they work with distributor and understand the trade) or with B2B selling experience.
 
For the other role, we need someone slightly more junior that can grow within Tetra Pak. The requirement will be similar as above."

Date added: 2016-05-27 || Action: Client Visit || Eddie, Executive Chairman of Dignitas, has been in Myanmar for about 5 years now. 
Has business in Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand, Singapore, Vietnam, South Korea and China. Frequent travel to SG, SK, China for a couple of days to overview the situation as the MDs out there perform well. But in Myanmar, he has to be hands on so wants GM to take care of it. 

Original plan was to open a hotel, but couldn't do it due to strict regulation on land buying and rental from the government. So chose similar business - car rental. Main customers are corporates like PTT and Telenor, Embassies (Tonny Blair and delegates used their services). Contractors of hotels too including Sedona. Has 100 staff, recruited by word of mouth - not very skilled. 

Looking for GM and Chief Accountant/ Account Manager. 

GM prefer repats from Thai and with car rental experience. If not, who has managed factories before. Chinese Burmese fine too. If none in that, will consider expats - 
2nd Priorities Thai 
3rd Priorities Korean - for some unknown reasons, they are quicker in learning Burmese and is very adaptable
Must manage medium size company (50 - 150 staff)
Quite hands on and can understand doing business in Myanmar. 
Salary: 62,000 - 70,000 USD Gross (all inclusive)
No Singaporean (cannot do well in Myanmar as they are very specific in their areas of specialities), Caucasian (doesn't last long in the country) for this role. 

Reports to Eddie and MD (who is also a shareholder).
Has 6 departments - Admin, Mkt, Sales and Ops. Has 6 Ops Manager (ex military). 
Must be male in late thirties and early fourties in order to lead /influence the team. 

Chief Accountant/ Account Manager

Has 4 book keepers at the moment. Submit the accounts to German account and auditing firm monthly. So wants to bring that in outsourcing and submit the once a year for auditing purpose only. 
Minimum 5 yrs of experience
Repat from Sg preferred. 
Salary: 24000 USD

Praised German and Korean's hardworking culture. Said Canadian are cheaper than Malaysian. However, Malaysian lower their salary expectation when they come into Myanmar due to their limited expertise.

 || (Chloe Williamson)Client Visit: Nice guy - quite punchy and obviously very senior in TPG. Looking atter supply chain and procurement function for investments globally. 

Head of SC for IBTC now is Aung Kyaw Moe (procurement and logistics together), new hire of a lady called Nandar (head of procurement) who reports to AKM. She is in her 30's, young and excited, very talented but over her head, most of her direct reports are more traditional and focused on delivery and chasing vendors. They have launched an E-vendor project which is the firts of its kind in Myanmar, its allining new vendors and monitoring existing vendors. The new role is focusing on the economics, so identifying new vendors, managing productivity and analyzing all existing vendors for the business - pricing and valuing analysis. 

It needs to be someone who can help nanadar train and develp her team, ideally from an MNC environment, procurement background. English most important, idelaly repat could be expat. Global skills set and needs to be able to handle all international suppliers, as well as the few in Myanmar (EG Broken rice which is a major feed stock). 

This needs ot be a hire that does not push nandar out of a job, they dont want to slit the team at this stage and currently its already split by category - eg bottles, lables, caps. nandar has 13 years of expeirnece in total. target Unilever, P&G, Coke, Nesle etc. Need CV's by next Thursday. 

This person would get the international training as they would be invited to the chief procurement summit for TPG in Shanghai each year also.

 || (Jolyn Ingson)Client Visit: Du Sar Mee and I met with Mr. Tan at Park Royal Hotel.
Mr Tan is a consultant for BMM -- a joint venture of Behn Meyer, Mitsui and Myanmar Agribusiness Public  to establish a new company, Agri First (AFC), to manufacture and distribute imported fertilisers in Myanmar.

He is looking for GM who is local not over 50 years old who has at least 10 years experience in Agriculture products. He wants top-caliber candidate to start the business. After this position is placed, they would be looking for head of all other departments. They are looking to grow the employees to 100 over the next year. They will start planning and placing other roles after the GM is placed and will start operations next year. They are on the process of getting their licence. 

As part of the plan, AFC expects to invest nearly JPY1.2bn ($184m) to build a fertiliser manufacturing plant, including a warehouse and other related facilities in the Thilawa Special Economic Zone.

Mr. Tan will be peruse the terms and conditions we proposed and will get back for how to proceed.

 || (Ngwar Bo Mee)Client Visit: Had a chat over the phone with Jirasit. 

Rockworth PLC, supplier of office furniture from Thailand.

Exporting office furniture to Myanmar (emphasizing more due to booming state), Laos, Cambodia and Vietnam. Has four 4 Sales Director Regionally. 

Local dealer is Kay Thu Madi. Been working with them for a couple of years. Looking for a Project Manager for Myanmar Dealer. Project Manager will directly report to Local Dealer. Necessary training will be provided in Thailand. 

Candidate must be working in an industry related to Real estate agent, interior designer, building contractor,  building developer and must have good connection with people in these business fields and speaks Burmese and English. 

Can be someone who has min 5 yrs of experience and a developer or real-estate agent with strong sales background, aggressive, assertive and punchy.

Has around 10 staffs in dealer office. 


Salary range is flexible based on candidates skill sets and capabilities.

RE: Rockworth: Project Sale Manager

Dear Chloe,
 
Were from Rockworth PLC, supplier of office furniture from Thailand. Currently our dealer in Yangon is urgently looking for a candidate who can be qualified as our new Project Sale Manager, brief requirement is as following
1.       Burmese nationality

2.       Able to communicate fluently in English

3.       Minimum 5 years of experience as sale manager or equivalence

4.       This person must be working in an industry related to Real estate agent, interior designer, building contractor,  building developer and must have good connection with people in these business fields

 
This person is to be based in Yangon and work together with our dealer there. Kindly advise us what is the possibility of finding the candidate with above requirements and timeframe, also cost of your service fee.
 
Looking forward for your soonest reply.

kept getting more donors, U.K. Sweden, us and even Korea was funding the DVB. 
Still have some of the core donors but as country is opening up the. The funding is dropping off.
Transitioning from funded organization into the commercial opartion.

Sky net and forever group only two with the expanding advertising growth

The only independent national news channel

chairman is expecting a lot from him.

From there, they will see if they will consider him.
*see note on christian

other candidates: he said they will see first the presentation of Christian then decide if they will consider the other 2.

invoice: after meeting with the board. I have to reiterate that is not the agreement and besides 1 candidate has had face to face meeting with the chairman already. He said, what will happen if these candidates you have sent will not pass, what will you do? Will you give more candidates? I said no, those we submitted are the best ones. they have been shortlisted among many we have contacted. They have experiences in different countries even higher than a CMO role.
 In the end he said, he will speak with the CFO.
Date added: 2016-10-19 || Action: Outbound Call || Feedback on Parkinai after face-face interview. They like him, but He is not at par with the other 2 candidates. He would be good for a manager position.

Victor and Noel: They are considering flying them both for a face-face interview. 

Christian -  waiting for the feedback on the second interview with Kevin.

If Christian is good, they will meet the 3 of them here in Yangon.

Invoice - He said he is facing a problem with the CFO. He is not willing until they do the face to face interview.

Will send him email to show his CFO.

Date added: 2016-10-11 || Action: Outbound Call || called to talk about the invoice but was reverted to a recording.
I believe he is in Bangkok. Will send him email instead.
Date added: 2016-08-25 || Action: Outbound Call || Called to follow up on Nitin Khurana. He said he will not be good for his company because he does not have marketing background. I explained that he has head sales and marketing team in his previous job and he also took courses in marketing.  Then he said it is not ok because of his availability. Nitin is going away in 2 weeks but will consider a meeting through Skype. 
My thoughts are the other candidate is also an Indian and his salary compared Nitin is only half.

He asked if I can also look for a candidate of Chinese origin.

I asked for another week for a new search.
Date added: 2016-08-25 || Action: Outbound Call || Spoke with him again yesterday and said he will only consider the Mr. Inamdar.. he referred to him as the foreign one/Indian guy. He said the other 2--the local ones, have experience in different industries. I pointed out that they are exactly in the same industry and been doing such in years. He just answered, he will only consider meeting the Indian guy. He also asked for 1 more before they set an interview.

He sent an email saying they will only interview 1 time so the more candidates the better.

Called again today to check his feedback on the new additional candidate i sent. he will call back as he did not see it yet.
Date added: 2016-08-23 || Action: Outbound Call || Saw the the profiles of the shortlisted candidates and like 2 of them and would like to arrange a meeting with them. He could not remember the names and as he is not in the office so he cannot pull them up. He said he will call back.

Date added: 2016-08-19 || Action: Outbound Call || Update on the search: told him I am sending him shortlist of candidate by Tuesday next week-- 23 August.

Reporting line is him. 50 people for the S&M Manager to lead in the Sales and Marketing department.
The station is in Mandalay. They do not have plans yet in having an office in Yangon even with their increase in production.

 || (Jolyn Ingson)Client Visit: Spoke with Phillip Low (Group HR - SEA) through phone on Monday, 10 October.

Santen is dsitributing eye-care products - specialized pharmaceutical products manufactured in Japan.

They want to set up their office in Myanmar in Jaunary next year, but sooner if they can.
They want it to be manned by 2 people in the beginning:
a Business Unit Manager and an Assistant. And they want to have them by November to mid-December.

Before then, they would like to understand labor law, social security system and pay roll. He wanted to know if Aquila can provide pay roll (I already asked Chloe that same day and she said no).

They will be using DKSH as their distributor in Myanmar.

The BUM will be managing sales (take care of P&L), expand their portfolio, and has to have business acumen.
They will send the complete JD after we sign terms.

Interviews will be done on the phone first then face-face when they come here.

He said we are too expensive and our services is being offered by other agencies they have spoken.
His decision will be based on the fees.
Will get back to me.

 || (Jolyn Ingson)Client Visit: Spoke with Jet Low over phone on Tuesday.
Define is a system integrator company in Malaysia with 15 people.

They have a rep office in Vietnam and partner in Singapore.
They would like to set up in Myanmar then later on go to Cambodia.
They want to open a small office with 1-2 people for the first 6 months then will open a bigger one with warehouse, proper environment for installations and other things.
They will start will trading and then installations later on.

They are looking for a Sales Manager to start and look after the office here. This person will be first flown to KL for 2-4 week training.
Qualifications: experience in the same industry or similar, English language, preferably a Myanmar person. An expat is ok as logn as he has experience in Myanmar.
Benefits: salary will depend on the market, initial training in KL.
They will need one as soon as possible.

Will send him our retained terms and wait for his decision.
